a man who stocked his home with more than 
6000 pints of homemade wine accidentally cut himself on a bottle 
and bled to death authorities say 
junius huggins 67 cut a fourinch gash across his left wrist 
and severed an artery as he apparently tried to tighten or remove 
the top of one of the wine bottles april 10 said county coroner 
jimmy gregg 
he left a trail of blood to his neighbors home where he sought 
help and died behind the house gregg said 
police confiscated 6100 pints of wine in bottles kegs and jugs 
we have no proof he had intentions of selling it for all i 
know it could have been a hobby of his making wine sheriffs 
capt wayne jeffords said monday 
the shed at his home where the wine was stored was covered with 
spraypainted biblical verses and biblical quotations were 
displayed around the property but jeffords said he didnt know who 
put them there 
