<TEXT>
france has had 11 citizens held hostage in the 
middle east and it has managed to free them all 
commentators are asking whether it is a gallic flair for 
diplomacy or cynical deals with terrorists and their sponsors that 
account for frances success 
is there as one commentator here asked a special french method 
that can maneuver around the obstacle that others run into 
france makes an important distinction said bassma 
kodmonidarwish an expert on frenchmiddle east relations it 
doesnt bargain with terrorist groups it negotiates with states 
each time hostages come home top government officials find 
themselves denying that france panders to terrorists 
and its true it cannot be criticized on that count said 
ms darwish who works for the french institute for international 
relations but it is also a hypocritical nation 
france came under fire from many prominent western newspapers 
for lauding col moammar gadhafi of libya for his role in securing 
the release tuesday of frenchwoman jacqueline valente her belgian 
companion and their child 
the three were held for more than two years by the 
libyancontrolled fatahrevolutionary council headed by terrorist 
abu nidal 
detractors draw little distinction between abu nidals group and 
gadhafi 
france did 
foreign minister roland dumas who praised gadhafis noble and 
humanitarian gesture in seeking the trios freedom and promised 
improved relations said france did not talk with the abductors 
he denied that france traded three jetfighters returned to 
libya several weeks ago for the hostages 
france negotiated the freedom of 10 of its 11 hostages in 
198688 when conservative premier jacques chirac was in power 
eighteen hostages of other nationalities remain in captivity in 
lebanon including eight americans the longestheld is terry 
anderson chief middle east correspondent for the associated press 
who was kidnapped march 16 1985 
the us government has publicly refused to negotiate for the 
release of its hostages but three americans were freed in 198586 
while us arms were secretly delivered to iran which backs groups 
holding hostages in lebanon reports of the deliveries led to the 
disclosure that some of profits were funneled to the contra rebels 
fighting the leftist sandinistas in nicaragua 
french thankyous that followed the release of its hostages were 
never so effusive as those proffered to gadhafi but france has 
also made concessions to iran for earlier releases 
all but one item on irans shopping list was met by the french 
who expelled top iranian dissident massoud rajavi normalized 
relations with iran and repaid part of a billion dollar debt dating 
to the days of the shah 
the only outstanding demand is freeing anis naccache serving a 
life sentence in france for the attempted 1980 assassination of the 
exiled former iranian premier shahpour bakhtiar 
gadhafi called for freedom for middle eastern political 
prisoners in europe and it remains to be seen whether naccache 
will go free 
the true french art is hypocrisy columnist richard cohen 
wrote this week in the washington post the french prattle on 
like a womanizer saying whatever seems effective at the moment at 
this particular moment gadhafi seems in line for the legion of 
honor he freed three hostages 
hypocrisy was a word often used abroad each time france obtained 
the release of hostages but the french view themselves differently 
there is here a certain resigned tolerance for halftruths or 
halflies for reasons of state perhaps more so than elsewhere 
the leftist daily liberation said in an editorial 
la raison detat is a famous phrase in france used by 
governments as an excuse to remain silent 
the 1985 sinking of the greenpeace flagship the rainbow 
warrior in new zealand in which one person was killed proved one 
of frances biggest debacles in decades 
international pressure eventually overcame reasons of state 
and the truth came out but polls at the time revealed a public far 
more outraged by the bungling of french spies than by their 
murderous task 
france has shown concerned nations it was prepared to negotiate 
to release hostages said ms darwish but she added that each time 
french hostages have been freed the political context was favorable 
public pressure was a determining factor in freeing french 
hostages held by iranianbacked groups ms darwish said 
the last three hostages held by iranianbacked groups were 
released may 4 1988 days before the presidential election the 
gambit did not work for chirac who lost to the incumbent francois 
mitterrand 
chiracs government denied charges it made payments or promised 
to free naccache as iran claimed the current socialist government 
says it can find no written record of any deals 
in the latest release of hostages the return of the three 
mirages held in france under an embargo was but a signal for change 
in frenchlibyan relations she said a more moderate stance by 
gadhafi over the past six months including his willingness to 
renew ties with egypt ripened the political climate 
it is that evolution which is more important than the 
hostages she said its not just a deal libya has evolved 
we did not exchange three hostages for three mirages but for 
two epithets said one french official referring to the words 
noble and humanitarian used to describe gadhafi 
in any event it had to be done said a foreign ministry 
spokesman it is the custom 
