<TEXT>
the next time new york is looking for a new 
nickname or something catchy to put on its license plates how 
about this tops in wollastonite 
thats right folks the empire state which likes to think 
itself unique in many ways is the wollastonite capital of the 
united states if not the world in fact new york was the only 
state that mined the stuff last year and the reason we know this 
is the us bureau of mines says so in its annual state minerals 
summaries 1990 
now maybe youre wondering what the heck wollastonite is the 
bureau of mines report doesnt say so lets try websters 
dictionary 
ah yes wollastonite a white monoclinic mineral casio3 a 
native calcium silicate it was named for william h wollaston 
an english physicist 
the bureau of mines report does offer tantalizing tidbits about 
new yorks wollastonite industry 
in late 1988 it tells us nyco a division of processed 
minerals inc announced that they made a significant discovery of 
wollastonite at oak hill a few miles from nycos existing mine at 
lewis drilling at the site which was initiated in 1986 indicated 
that the new deposit would double the companys current reserves 
the federal report continues albeit ungrammatically during 
the year nyco also introduced wollastokups a chemically modified 
for use in wollastonite product engineering thermoplastics for 
fascia and body panels 
fascia body panels wollastokups 
now wait a minute 
a fascia plural fasciae according to the dictionary is a 
flat strip or an instrument panel or dashboard and anyone 
who has ever had a car accident knows what body panels are so we 
may be getting warm 
todd hutchins a machine operator at nycos lewis mine in the 
adirondacks confirmed that the company sells wollastonite to car 
manufacturers in addition to being used in dashboards and body 
panels wollastonite reinforces car bumpers and is a component of 
brake discs and pads he said asked for a definition of 
wollastokups hutchins said its the same stuff but its 
chemically treated to make it stronger 
