mexico and hungary but its only mined in new yorks essex 
county according to the encyclopedia americana 
wollastonite is also used as a paint filler and in ceramic 
products such as electrical insulators tiles and porcelain the 
encyclopedia says 
the minerals namesake william hyde wollaston was quite a guy 
born in 1766 in east dereham norfolk england he earned a medical 
degree from cambridge university according to the encyclopedia 
entry written by l pearce williams a history professor from 
cornell university 
