soft enough to be shaped his efforts were successful and his 
fortune assured williams writes from 1802 until his death a 
whole host of discoveries flowed from his laboratory 
for example williams tells us wollaston discovered two new 
metals palladium in 1803 and rhodium in 1804 but williams does 
not say wollaston discovered wollastonite nor does he tell us who 
decided to name the stuff after him 
the mystery continues 
