few developments would make american rice 
farmers happier than to see japan open its door to imports 
agriculture secretary clayton yeutter predicts it will happen this 
year 
for decades the united states has been badgering japan to open 
its import door to more agricultural products there has been 
significant success with beef citrus and some other products 
but rice no way 
rice has almost mystical status as a food staple in japan and 
