posted notices announcing the expulsions of movement leaders wuer 
kaixi and chai ling both of whom escaped to the west 
students appeared more concerned with making the most of 
sundays sunshine and warm temperatures reading outdoors or 
playing basketball than with attempting to mark the anniversary 
the communist partys official peoples daily did not mention 
the anniversary in its sunday edition there have been no reported 
official events to commemorate the death of hu 
