15900 yen and 15945 yen after opening at 15915 yen 
in the bond market the price of the benchmark no 119 10year 
government bond was quoted at 8579 points at 300 pm down from 
its close friday at 8590 the bond yield rose to 7405 percent 
from 7380 percent 
kazuhiro nomura an analyst for new japan securities co said 
arbitrage selling of spot issues accounted for the deep losses in 
the nikkei index which were further exaggerated by the unusually 
light trading 
in arbitrage trading dealers exchange spot issues for stock 
futures or vice versa in an attempt to profit from the difference 
in prices between the two markets 
japanese market participants have frequently pointed to the 
recent introduction of arbitrage techniques as a reason for the 
continuing instability of the tokyo market 
nomura said market dealers were largely waiting on the sidelines 
ahead of an announcement wednesday by the us commerce department 
of the countrys trade figures for february they were also waiting 
to see the bank of japans moves to regulate the countrys money 
supply and the trend in exchange rates 
on the currency market dealers also pointed to the us trade 
figure announcement and speculation about future bank of japan 
policy regarding interest rates as affecting the yendollar rate 
norio takeda a dealer with the bank of tokyo said the dollars 
early strength was attributable to the view that the upcoming us 
monthly trade imbalance will show an improvement 
a dealer with fuji bank speaking on condition of anonymity 
added the dollar was also propped up by a large demand for the 
currency by banks on occasion of the first day of the monthly 
reserveaccounting period monday 
early in the reserve period banks try to obtain a lot of cash 
to fufill their reserve requirements the surge in demand often 
kicks up demand for the dollar as well as various short term 
interest rates 
