following are excerpts from the vatican 
translation of pope john paul iis easter sunday message which was 
delivered in italian 
 
i have overcome the world jn 1633 
the stone before the tomb at the foot of golgotha rolled away 
the tomb itself empty he is not here he has risen he is not 
here mk 166 
go tell his disciples and peter mk 167 
simon peter and john discover in the tomb everything just as 
the women had said they do not find him were they perhaps 
already then capable of recalling those words i have overcome the 
world in the world you have tribulation but be of good cheer i 
have overcome the world jn 1633 yes those last days had been 
a time of terrible tribulation they had been dismayed by the 
arrest in gethsemane by the condemnation to the cross by the 
death on calvary they had experienced a terrible tribulation 
before the empty tomb did they wonder has he conquered the world 
 
this world in which man lives where man has dominion this 
world in the end seems to overcome man it overcomes him through 
death but christ who has conquered death has overcome the 
world by his own death he has put to death that death whose 
beginning was sin mans sin and the sin of the world 
the world as the original lie was whispered became in mans 
heart gods foe the world which should have opened mans heart to 
god began instead to drive god out of the human heart and even 
though the tempter has repeated from the beginning you will be 
like god cf gen 35 this world is never able to offer man in 
the end anything more anything other than death 
in the world you have tribulation but be of good cheer that 
world which is the theatre of mans historycarries the marks of 
his energies his tragedies and his triumphs gaudium et spes 2 
the worldthe scene of mans many tribulations has fallen into 
the bondage of sin ibid and so often calls this very bondage its 
freedom the world called into existence out of love and kept in 
existence by its creator by christ on the cross freed by the 
power of his death and revealed anew through his resurrection as 
the divine cosmos cf ibid 
man of our time man living immersed in the world thinking that 
you have mastered it whereas you may well be its victim christ 
frees you from every form of bondage to set you upon the way to 
victory over self to love that is constructive and aims for the 
good a love that is demanding that makes you build up and not 
destroy your tomorrow your family your environment and all of 
society 
man of our time only the risen christ can fully satisfy your 
irrepressible yearning for freedom after the horrors of two world 
wars and all the wars which in these last fifty years often in the 
name of godless ideologies have reaped a harvest of victims and 
sown hatred in so many nations after the years of dictatorships 
which have deprived men and women of their basic freedoms the true 
dimensions of the spirit have been discovered anew those 
dimensions which the church has always promoted by revealing in 
christ mans true stature 
today as well the reawakening of many democracies is leading to 
dialogue and trust between peoples and the world is coming to 
understand once again that man cannot live without god without the 
truth that in him makes him free cf jn 832 
man of our time christ sets you free from selfishness to call 
you to a spirit of sharing and to a ready and joyful commitment to 
others i have been in africa in the sahel and i have seen the 
sand burying villages drying up wells burning the eyes turning 
children into skeletons paralyzing the strength of the young as 
it brings desperation starvation sickness and death death from 
hunger and thirst man of today wealthy nations of the 
civilisation of opulence do not be indifferent to this great 
tragedy be ever more urgently resolved to help those peoples who 
struggle each day for survival let yourselves be convinced that 
there can be no freedom where misery continues to exist 
let human and christian solidarity be the challenge that 
provokes your conscience to make that sand slowly give way to the 
advancement of human dignity an abundance of bread and the return 
of laughter employment hope and progress yet i thank god that i 
have also seen volunteers individuals associations and 
institutions priests religious laity of various professions 
committing themselves and making sacrifices for the good of their 
brothers and sisters who are most lonely and most sorely tried i 
thank them in the name of the crucified and risen lord 
man of our time christ frees you because he loves you because 
he has given himself for you cf gal 220 because he has won 
victory for you and for all people 
