nasa says it has completed the 
trickiest part of preparations for the second attempt to launch 
space shuttle discovery with the hubble space telescope 
the space agency on saturday removed a faulty auxiliary power 
unit that forced a scrub of discoverys launch last tuesday a new 
unit was installed sunday the first time the procedure has been 
performed at the launch pad 
also on saturday discoverys payload bay doors were opened and 
hubbles six nickelhydrogen batteries were removed for recharging 
at a laboratory the 130hour recharging began around noon sunday 
nasa took the batteries to the lab because they can be recharged 
at a cooler temperature there than at the launch pad and thus 
retain more power 
nasa spokesman george diller said the weekend operations were 
the trickiest part of preparation for the second launch attempt 
