they mowed the lawn did the gardening said lt thomas 
johnston commander of the westchester police narcotics unit 
what they did was ruin the neighborhood 
the family paid the rent and all other bills by cash and used 
fake names 
neighbors spotted at least two children but nobody is sure how 
many there were the children were not sent to schools and the 
family was seen only on weekends 
during the week a light was on and no one suspected anything 
they blended in and no one was any wiser said johnston 
no one ever saw deliveries being made said johnston but the 
chemicals probably were brought in in small quantities 
