tetrachloroethene acetone toluene and dichloroethene which comes 
from tetrachloroethene 
the chemicals are used for processing cocaine but have 
industrial uses such as for dry cleaning but police say they are 
leaning toward the drug processing theory 
rocco a mastronardi jr assistant county public health 
engineer said his department was checking wells in the area 
where homes range from 300000 to 400000 
samples from the well and septic system taken in march contained 
4000 parts per billion of the tetrachloroethene and 14000 per 
billion of dichloroethene officials said quantities above 5 parts 
per billion are considered hazardous with longterm exposure 
owner max marx and one neighbor have been filtering their well 
water for drinking 
the pollution has seeped to the leaching field and affected 
