criticized those who advocate slamdunk solutions to global 
warming 
we cannot sail blindly into the future said bromley 
another conference cochairman 
some computer models have suggested that manmade pollutants will 
cause a 4degree to 9degree fahrenheit increase in global 
temperatures in 60 years as the increasing pollution traps heat 
close to the earth 
however some scientists said those projections are uncertain 
and may not adequately take into account clouds or other factors 
that might have a counteracting effect 
