<TEXT>
angolan rebels monday claimed their 
forces killed 78 soldiers destroyed 92 military vehicles and shot 
down two helicopters belonging to the marxist government in two 
days of fighting 
the heaviest clashes occurred saturday in the province of uige 
150 miles northeast of the angolan capital luanda the rebels said 
in a statement distributed in lisbon they said guerrillas ambushed 
a convoy of military vehicles there 
the usbacked unita rebels claimed to have destroyed 70 
vehicles and killed 43 government troops in the raid two of four 
helicopters taking part in the fighting were destroyed by rebel 
antiaircraft fire said the unita statement 
the angolan defense ministry said a sovietbuilt mi17 
helicopter was downed by the rebels killing three crew members 
but said another mi17 escaped with minor damage 
unita has vowed to step up its activities in northern angola in 
response to the governments advance into its southeastern 
territories in december 
mondays rebel statement said 35 government soldiers died in 
three clashes with unita forces on the southern front over friday 
and saturday 
western and angolan diplomats in lisbon said monday no date or 
venue had been set for peace talks between unita and the government 
to end the guerilla conflict now in its 15th year 
unconfirmed reports last week said direct negotiations between 
the two sides could start soon in lisbon unita proposed the 
portuguese capital as a venue for talks but the government said it 
would prefer the west african nation of cape verde 
both sides have expressed a desire for talks aimed at a 
ceasefire and a political solution to the conflict 
a ceasefire agreed to last summer and tentative peace talks 
broke down within weeks 
unita the national union for the total independence of angola 
has been fighting since the country gained independence from 
portugal in 1975 to force the cuban and sovietbacked government to 
share power 
</TEXT>
