<TEXT>
milk production in the first three months of 
1990 was up about 1 percent from the first quarter of last year 
the agriculture department said monday 
the us total was reported at about 369 billion pounds in the 
first quarter compared with less than 365 billion pounds a year 
earlier 
in the 21 major dairy states which account for about 85 percent 
of the us total output was reported at 313 billion pounds the 
number of cows on farms was shown at 851 million head down 27000 
from a year earlier 
the average milk output per cow in the 21 states was 1291 
pounds in march up 23 pounds from march 1989 
department analysts forecast us milk production this year may 
rise 1 percent to 3 percent from last years 1443 billion pounds 
the high milk prices of late 1989 and early 1990 have provided 
a financial boost to dairy farmers and a stimulus to production 
the departments economic research service said 
</TEXT>
