the spanish commander of a united nations peacekeeping force in 
the honduran town of sirsitara about 40 miles from the nicaraguan 
border 
the fighters were members of yatama an organization of miskito 
suma and rama indians from nicaraguas caribbean coast they have 
been fighting the sandinistas since 1981 
forty venezuelan soldiers in the un force set about destroying 
the rebel weapons mainly sovietdesigned ak47 assault rifles 
it is a sad day for us but the decision has been taken 
yamata chief serafino bencie told reporters as his men 
surrendered their arms 
quesada gomez said each rifle will be cut into three pieces and 
then blown up with explosives 
