<TEXT>
the us supreme court on monday refused 
to hear an appeal from a man condemned to die for killing an 
attorney during a 1985 courthouse shootout 
the justices denied ronnie lee gardners bid for a supreme court 
hearing without comment except for customary dissenting statements 
by justices william j brennan and thurgood marshall who oppose 
capital punishment under all circumstances 
gardner 27 was sentenced to die for gunning down michael j 
burdell during a botched escape attempt april 2 1985 at salt lake 
citys metropolitan hall of justice 
police said a girlfriend of gardners slipped him a handgun 
while he was being transported to a hearing on a separate 
seconddegree murder charge stemming from the 1984 slaying of a 
bartender 
though shackled hand and foot gardner turned the weapon on two 
utah state prison guards accompanying him one of the guards shot 
gardner in the shoulder before he fled confronted burdell and shot 
the attorney once in the head gardner also wounded a bailiff 
before surrendering 
in february 1989 the utah supreme court denied gardners appeal 
following a threeyear review 
defense attorneys had argued that gardner should have been 
granted a change of venue due to pretrial publicity his lawyers 
also contended that the state district judge who tried the case 
should have removed himself since he was in the courthouse at the 
time of gardners escape attempt 
gardners attorneys were not immediately available for comment 
on the latest decision 
