<TEXT>
the manufacturer of the steel tubes suspected to 
be parts of a huge iraqi weapon said monday its contract with iraq 
involved space research corp which designed a satellite launch 
system and was run by slain american ballistics expert gerald bull 
customs seized the eight sections april 12 as they were to be 
shipped to iraq and insist they could be used as part of a large 
gun sheffield forgemasters has insisted they were for use in a 
petrochemical installation and not subject to the licensing 
controls that bar sales of armaments to iraq 
forgemasters lawyer stuart benson said in a statement monday 
all documents i have seen support forgemasters understanding 
that the pipes were for a petrochemical application 
it has always been accepted by forgemasters that space 
research corp had involvement in this contract forgemasters has 
never sought to conceal such involvement 
he said a dr cowley not bull was the space research 
representative in the contract with the iraqi ministry of trade 
space research has its headquarters in brussels 
customs said there was no question the tubes could be used as a 
barrel of a large artillery piece to fire a projectile it holds 
the tubes pending investigation 
benson said it was not for forgemasters to prove or disprove the 
ultimate use and purpose of the tubes 
my only concern is to rebut any suggestion that it has acted 
in any way improperly or unlawfully he said 
bull 62 a canadianborn us citizen was slain in brussels 
march 22 belgian police said he was shot twice in the head with a 
silenced gun and robbery was not the motive because 20000 was 
found in bulls pockets 
bulls company was described as a multinational dealing in space 
and military research and employed in international arms sales 
sheffield forgemasters says it agreed to supply 52 sections of 
the steel tubing and had delivered 44 to the ministry of industry 
and minerals in baghdad it denied the eight tubes seized last week 
could be joined together to form a huge gun to attack iraqs middle 
east enemies or launch satellites 
iraq says the tubes are petrochemical pipes 
on saturday press association the british domestic news 
agency quoted unidentified reliable government sources as 
saying they had correspondence linking british industry with bulls 
firm 
