defense minister oscar botero said monday he did not know if the 
statement was authentic but that a split in the cartel does exist 
over tactics in a battle against the government 
there are many drug traffickers botero said in a tv 
interview broadcast by the cinevision news program adding that 
some members of the medellin cartel were opposed to terrorist 
violence 
the statement was issued sunday night and declared 
we the extraditables do not agree with the terrorist acts that 
pablo escobar is ordering in an indiscriminate and personal way 
previously we asked pablo escobar to stop detonating bombs and 
executing innocent people because such acts did not help our cause 
from now on we declare ourselves in total disagreement with 
the terrorist acts ordered personally by pablo escobar we reject 
the violent way escobar is forcing us to carry on his personal 
war by kidnapping torturing and threatening our families 
authorities have blamed the medellin cartel for a campaign of 
bombings and other terrorist violence that killed 238 people in the 
last eight months 
the attacks were in retaliation for a government crackdown in 
which 15 drug suspects were extradited and hundreds of traffickers 
properties seized 
last month the cartel ended a unilateral truce declared in 
january it said the renewed violence was in reply to continued 
government pressure on them 
in two weeks terrorists killed 28 police officers in medellin 
on april 5 police defused a 1650pound dynamite truck bomb on a 
main avenue in bogota during morning rush hour authorities say the 
bomb could have killed thousands 
authorities blamed the medellin cartel for all the attacks the 
statement makes it appear that escobar may have acted alone 
police dispatched 300 antiterrorist agents to medellin to 
search for escobar who they say has undergone plastic surgery to 
evade authorities 
police sources say escobars capture dead or alive is imminent 
since he is losing organization support authorities say escobar 
has killed and tortured cartel members suspected of betraying him 
</TEXT>
