<TEXT>
polands lawmakers on april 11 formally 
ended censorship one of the final relics of four decades of 
communist rule 
the decision by a 2660 vote with eight abstentions was 
largely symbolic censorship has been almost nonexistent since the 
solidarityled government of prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki was 
voted in to power last fall 
solidarity deputy juliusz braun said censorship had actually 
allowed slandering with impunity without permitting a person to 
defend himself 
the censorship law allowed the former communist authorities to 
control all kinds of publications and stage and film performances 
preventing criticism of the political system 
many poles turned to underground printing which flourished 
through the 1980s 
solidarity the east blocs first independent trade union 
fought for elimination of censorship since its foundation in 1980 
</TEXT>
