the korean peninsula was divided into 
north korea and south korea in 1945 at the end of world war ii in 
the four decades since the south has had five leaders while the 
north has been dominated by only one 
kim il sung 78 president of north korea is the longest 
governing ruler in the communist world and the object of a slavish 
personality cult which revers him as great leader kims son 
kim jong il has been groomed to succeed him in what would be the 
first communist dynasty 
capitalist south korea was first administered by the american 
military government in 1948 elections were held and south korea 
elected syngman rhee as president of the nations first republic 
government 
south koreas government is divided roughly into five periods 
the last three heads of state were generals or former generals 
changes in governments were sometimes turbulent and one president 
park chunghee was assassinated 
here is the list of south koreas leaders 
syngman rhee first republic 19481960 
chang myon second republic 19606l 
park chunghee third and fourth republic 19621980 
chun doohwan fifth republic 19801988 
roh taewoo sixth republic 1988present 
