<TEXT>
as long as two football fields endtoend its 
the worlds largest sailing ship now in service the recently 
launched club med i will sail the caribbean in the winter and the 
mediterranean in the summer with a cargo of mostly young adults 
looking for fun and games and dont worry if there is no wind the 
sails are just boosters for its diesel engines 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
when a sudden blow came up on 
the spanish main the other day no bearded bosun bellowed all 
hands aloft to bend canvas reef and furl sail 
the captain just pushed a button and the computer located behind 
the wheelhouse rolled up the seven enormous sails like window 
shades and in seconds set about controlling the list of the worlds 
largest sailing ship now in service 
i am in love with this ship she maneuvers just like a fish 
enthused alain lambert captain of the recently launched club med 
i presiding over a console of dials scopes and screens even in 
the roughest seas she just stays on the waves on the passage from 
the canaries to cape verde during our maiden voyage in january we 
had 40knot winds and the computer reduced sail perfectly 
as we headed toward the us virgin islands on one leg of a 
sevenday cruise out of guadeloupe with 220 passengers on board a 
weathered old schooner with dingy brown sails crossed our bow the 
captain spoke her with a friendly blast on the foghorn 
for me this is something glorious a whole new life he 
said studying a yellow screen that in dancing graphics showed the 
sails receding on the five aluminum masts and the booms changing 
position its like going back a century to find a passenger ship 
that looks like a ship and not like a floating soapbox notice 
wherever we go they admire us 
sure enough as we entered the harbor at charlotte amalie a 
whole flotilla of yachts fishing smacks sightseeing craft even a 
straying ferry ventured near to ogle us the way the south sea 
islanders circled captain james cooks hms endeavour in their 
outrigger canoes 
at anchor a huge stern ramp was lowered like a world war ii 
landing craft to disgorge an armada of waterski boats windsurf 
boards sailing sloops several boatloads of scuba divers 
shouldering air tanks and a school of webfooted snorkelers 
dr jeanyves siriez the ships surgeon led the diving party 
the german second mate uwe heidenreich took leave of the bridge 
to join the waterskiers 
meanwhile a long file of passengers some in tshirts 
proclaiming when the going gets tough the tough go shopping 
went down the long gangplank into the bobbing tenders for an 
assault on the duty free shops and posh restaurants of the us 
virgin island capital 
is this a cruise ship like dozens of others in caribbean 
waters offering the seagoing ambiance of shuffleboard glitzy 
floor shows bouillon at 11 on the sun deck and blacktie captains 
dinners 
or is it a floating club med village dedicated like the 110 
others around the globe to macho sports sumptuous buffet meals 
with wine casual dress and lifestyles in an atmosphere of 
ebullient camaraderie 
some of both 
village veterans on their first cruise wondered whether chef de 
village janyck daudet outranked the captain in the reception line 
at the welcoming cocktail party when the ships program decreed 
elegant dress for dinner some put their best foot forward in 
jogging sneakers 
cruise ship veterans spoiled by bigname las vegas acts on 
other ships were only moderately tolerant of the nightly amateur 
musicals staged by the exuberant staff in the superbly equipped 
theater for club med addicts the beachcomber fantasy was blurred 
a bit by using credit cards instead of beads to barter for drinks 
in the five bars 
there was a bridge instructor on duty in the card room but in 
deference to a younger more active cruising clientele there were 
no shuffleboard bingo or steeplechase races 
</TEXT>
