<TEXT>
stephanie zimbalist has gone from solving 
mysteries on television to creating one in caroline she plays 
a young woman who was presumed dead for 16 years before turning up 
to claim a family fortune 
caroline the seasons final hall of fame presentation on 
cbs on sunday is in reality a touching family drama masquerading 
as a mystery the story set in the 1950s appears sinister at 
first with caroline suspected of being an impostor out for the 
inheritance it then turns into something quite different 
its about how families work and dont work says zimbalist 
who starred for four seasons in the private eye series remington 
steele 
its a study of how families operate in a group its like a 
little boat if one person is dysfunctional it tips the boat 
you have a father who is a workaholic you have a mother whos 
a control freak you have a young girl whos handicapped you have 
a boy who has the one chance to become normal but hes attached to 
