<TEXT>
the works of leonore tawney whose magical incorporation of 
materials into her art made her one of the centurys leading fiber 
artists will be on show at the american craft museum in new york 
as part of the museums master artist series 
leonore tawney a retrospective opening april 18 will 
feature more than 100 works created over a 45year period the 
exhibit will chronicle her use of feathers eggs stone shells and 
weavings as well as abstract and figurative works in clay 
tawney was always an independent spirit who continuously 
