<TEXT>
citicorp on monday gave its 132 california 
branches the flagship citibank name 
the nations largest banking concern which is based in new 
york had been forced to keep its california operations separate 
since it began operating in the state in 1982 after acquiring san 
franciscobased fidelity savings 
but the barriers came down in last years thrift bailout law 
known as the financial institutions reform recovery and 
enforcement act or firrea 
california is not allowing the big commercial banks from new 
york inside its borders until 1991 but citicorp does not fall 
under that restriction because its state operations are chartered 
as a savings and loan formerly known as citicorp savings 
the citibank branches in california are now able to sell retail 
banking services to state residents who already conduct business 
with the company through its new york headquarters 
one example of the new freedom is the right for california 
branches to contact the 15 million residents who have a citibank 
credit card and attempt to sign them up for a checking or savings 
account 
the old regulations meant that the savings branches in 
california could not crossmarket to any customers with the new 
york branches the rigorous regulations forced citicorp to hire an 
independent electronic network to allow its california customers 
the use of automatic teller machines in new york 
there were a lot of people in california who didnt know that 
citicorp savings was part of the largest bank in the united 
states said david a brooks in charge of citicorps consumer 
banking in the west 
