for the three months ended march 31 ibm earned 103 billion 
or 181 per share compared with a profit of 950 million or 
161 a share in 1989 revenue rose 11 percent to 1418 billion 
from 1273 billion 
ibms results exceeded expectations of most analysts who were 
predicting earnings per share of between 135 and 170 ibm had 
been forecasting 155 to 165 a share profit some analysts said 
ibm closed up 375 to 11087 a share monday in active 
composite trading on the new york stock exchange 
the rise in ibm considered one of the most heavily weighted 
stocks in the dow jones industrial average of 30 bluechip 
companies helped boost the dow by 1126 to 276306 without it 
the dow which rose as much as 41 points before giving back some of 
its gains would have been little changed analysts said 
don young a computer analyst with sanford c bernstein amp co 
called ibms quarterly revenue gain its best in several years he 
also noted that operating income was up 33 percent to 213 billion 
from 160 billion expenses led by higher income taxes rose to 
1204 billion from 1112 billion 
but young stopped short of predicting a major turnaround for 
ibm which has seen its earnings and stock performance weaken in 
recent years 
the worlds largest computer maker was hurt by the dollars 
volatility and the companys difficulty in making transitions to 
new products it also has faced slow growth in demand for its big 
mainframe computers which were being overtaken by speedy personal 
computers and workstations 
william j milton jr a computer analyst with brown brothers 
harriman agreed it was too early to say ibm had turned the corner 
for good ibm has said nothing about a resurgence we do know 
from dealer surveys in recent months that ibm has been gaining 
market share in its personal computer share as far as demand for 
other products we dont know 
he said in the yearago quarter ibms earnings were depressed 
because a chip problem caused a delay in shipment of mainframe 
computers the biggest and most profitable part of ibms product 
line 
still market observers said mondays results helped push 
bluechip stocks higher by dispelling worries that first quarter 
corporate profits would be widely disappointing 
ibms results are among the first of a deluge of firstquarter 
earnings reports expected over the next several days analyst say 
the reports could have a major impact on the stock market in the 
near term 
ibm chairman john f akers said he was encouraged by the latest 
results 
our strategy of listening to our customers and improving the 
competitiveness of our products and services is working he said 
in a statement we are focusing our investments to take advantage 
of the opportunities in our industry and we are streamlining our 
operations while we improve our product line 
in the first quarter ibm introduced several products among 
them were its risc system6000 workstations aimed at capturing a 
share of the small but fastgrowing market for such machines 
the new machines have garnered favorable comments from industry 
analysts who called them impressive for their performance pricing 
and features 
the application of new technology to customers business 
problems is really the key to ibms future success said sam 
albert who runs the computer consulting firm sam albert associates 
inc of scarsdale ny 
those applications are starting to pay off 
