perlman after the company posted a net loss of 6804 million in 
1989 
he retired as a control data employee on march 15 and came 
under fire for entering retirement with a 424 million severance 
package after his fouryear reign yielded 9239 million in net 
losses and thousands of layoffs 
the 1989 financial report released by control data in march said 
the company laid off 7750 employees last year 
control data has been through a tumultuous period price 
said in a statement announcing that he will not seek reelection 
for the past decade the computer industry has undergone 
fundamental and irreversible change for many enterprises that has 
been fatal 
for control data the task of reshaping the company so that it 
has the potential for future profitability and growth has been 
long difficult and painful he said it is clear that under 
current circumstances my decision to withdraw from active 
management at this time is best for the company 
price 60 joined control data in 1961 as a computer programmer 
he became close to founder william norris and replaced him in 1986 
as chairman and chief executive 
price will not be replaced on the companys board and the size 
of the board will be reduced at the annual meeting to 10 directors 
the company said 
proxies will not be voted for price since he will no longer be a 
board nominee control data said adding that no new chairman will 
be named at this time 
shareholders of record were being notified of the change the 
company said 
bob price has served control data with commitment and loyalty 
for almost 30 years perlman said he has many contributions 
yet to make to the community in the areas of quality and of 
educational and technology policy 
